<span class="ez_quot">&gt; On Dec 29, 2010, at 9:12 AM, Chris Blow wrote:</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; hello, happy Christmas everyone,</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; to me, it makes sense to me to use an OSM baselayer as the default map for</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; several reasons:</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; - legal: keeps the default install free of licensing issues</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; - design: removes the google logo from the page</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; - UX: avoids the nagging API key error (which is always my first</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; experience upon installation)</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; - community: strengthens a partnership with OSM, some of our strongest and</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; most important friends IMO</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; thoughts?</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; Cheers</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt;</span>
<span class="ez_quot">&gt; c</span>
